<blockquote><p>As the orphans from the SIFA African Children’s Choir prepared to perform at a church in the West Side’s Lawndale neighborhood (approx. 94% Black) Sunday afternoon, someone stole “irreplaceable” items from the van the orphans tour in.</p>
<p>The choir had spent almost a week in Chicago when they arrived at the City of Refuge Ministries, located at 15th Street and Keeler Avenue in the Lawndale neighborhood, according to SIFA founder and director Carrie Harless.</p>
